answerText: George Gissing[10] That aforementioned novel by Gissing is titled "New" this place. It refers to an avenue in the Moorfields district of London known for its abundance of hack writers.

question: Question:  [10] Name this Naturalist English author of The Odd Women and The Nether World. Another novel by this author contrasts the lives of the writers Jasper Milvain and Edward Reardon.
